            "answer_text": "Mmm \u201cme\u201d being the objective form of the pronoun \u201cI\u201d, means that something (a verb, a preposition\u2026) acted on the pronoun \u201cI\u201d. So \u201cI was slapped by him\u201d=\u201dHe slapped me\u201d. With that in mind, if someone asks: \u201dWho wants to be slapped\u201d, a valid answer would be: \u201cMe\u201d (the one word sentence is a bonus). If you want to make it longer, you have flavors like \u201cMe, and everyone else on Quora\u201d, or \u201cMe, because I need to wake up\u201d, etc. :) ",
